Description: Tools and a Shiny application for exploring the bias-variance
    tradeoff in polynomial regression. Provides functions to generate
    synthetic regression data from smooth or wiggly true functions, fit
    polynomial models of varying degrees, compute mean squared error, and
    run Monte Carlo simulations to estimate squared bias and variance. The
    accompanying Shiny app offers an interactive visualization of how
    model complexity affects bias and variance.
